blog.name: coolchickzoutthere
blog.title: Katie B
blog.description: my life is just taylor swift and brooklyn nine nine at this point

body:
PSA

I love Taylor Swift with all my heart and she’s helped me through so many tough times. This year was probably the worst year I’ve ever had because of bullying and being in a school that was the wrong fit for me. I would go home on the bus, listening to the girl who was bullying me talk badly about other people, and me. But once reputation came out, I was able to get way closer with a girl who told me she liked Taylor Swift too. We would then listen to the album on the bus rides home, and it gave us something to talk about, and something to drown out the sounds of bullying. I know so many other people have much more difficult experiences, but Taylor and her music helped give me something to love, and to distract myself from my seemingly impossible day-to-day experiences. I’ve been seeing her in concert since I was around 9, and been an avid fan since before then. I remember clearing out my closet and sitting inside it on a pillow, with Long Live playing in my headphones on my iPod Shuffle. Posters of her covered my walls, and still form a collage on my closet doors. I have limited edition magazines and books about Taylor that I would read when I was little, and still read when I need to feel better. I have watched the LWYMMD music video and lyric video too many times to count, thanks to the Ticketmaster Verified Fan competition. But it was all worth it because knowing that I was seeing Taylor on July 14th, gave me something to keep in the back of my mind when someone said something mean. I just remembered how exciting it would be to see Taylor live for the first time since 1989. I am changing schools, so the end of the school year this year offered not only an ending to a horrible experience, but also opened the door to an amazing summer, where I would be going to the Reputation Stadium Tour. I could not be more excited, and I have no idea why I wrote this, other than to just hopefully tell Taylor how much she has helped me through such a rough year!

summary: I know I’m mostly preaching to the converted here, but I’m honestly so pissed off on Taylor behalf and for that reason you won’t...
body:
I know I’m mostly preaching to the converted here, but I’m honestly so pissed off on Taylor behalf and for that reason you won’t see any of those beach photos on my blog. She declines to take photos with a fan because she wants her holiday to remain a secret…. and they post her location online instead and then the paps show up? Honestly - there is more to life than showing off about your life. Taylor is a human being and you should just enjoy the moment of meeting her and respect her fucking right to privacy and a little life. It really isn’t that hard and it makes me so angry that people disrespect a woman that’s so good to us like this. Taylor is a human being, y’all.

Like imagine if we had all had that mentality - there’d have been no secret session. It’s about respecting celebrities as people and not social entities to be traded for status via your social media.
